Citation.sAbstract: The densities of (octane + benzene, or toluene, or 1,3-xylene, or 1,3,5-trimethylbenzene) were measured at temperatures (298.15,  308.15, 318.15, and 328.15) K by means of a vibrating-tube densimeter. The excess molar volumes V E  m calculated from the density data  provide the temperature dependence of V E  m in the temperature range of (298 to 328) K. The V E  m results were correlated using the fourthorder  Redlich Kister equation, with the maximum likelihood principle being applied for the determination of the adjustable parameters.  It was found that the values of V E  m are not very much dependent on temperature and in all cases decrease with the number of methyl  groups on benzene ring of the alkylbenzene.
Citation.sTitle: Excess molar volumes of (octane + benzene, or toluene, or 1,3-xylene, or 1,3,5-trimethylbenzene) at temperatures between (298.15 and 328.15) K
